<div>
  <p>Every seller has their own unique needs and principles when it comes to issuing refunds, therefore Gumroad allows and encourages its sellers to <a href="335-custom-refund-policy">set their own refund policies</a>.</p>
  <p>That said, Gumroad reserves the right to issue refunds within 90 days of purchase, at its discretion, to prevent chargebacks. If Gumroad support refunds a sale on your behalf, we'll email you to let you know, along with the reason for the refund.</p>
  <p>That said, you can set a "no-refunds" policy, but card networks still allow customers to file <a href="134-how-does-gumroad-handle-chargebacks">chargebacks</a> at any time. <strong>Too many successful disputes can put your Gumroad account at risk of suspension</strong>, even if your policy is clearly stated. </p>
  <p>If your account's dispute rate goes above 1% of your sales, the "No refunds allowed" option becomes unavailable in your settings. If your account is set to "No refunds allowed" at that point, Gumroad automatically updates it to a 30-day money-back guarantee; refund policies you already offer of 7 days or more stay as they are. Going forward you can pick any refund period of 7 days or longer. We'll email you if this happens, and refunding customers who ask is the fastest way to bring your dispute rate back down.</p>
  <p>If a customer is threatening a chargeback, we recommend that you offer them a <a href="47-how-to-refund-a-customer#partial">partial refund</a> using the feature we've provided you with. </p>
  <p>Learn more about our terms <a href="http://www.gumroad.com/terms">here</a>.</p>
  <p>And learn more about chargebacks <a href="134-how-does-gumroad-handle-chargebacks" rel="nofollow">here</a>.</p>
